Without further delay let's get started :)<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="https://www.yvonh.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/linux.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="544" data-original-width="800" height="434" src="https://www.yvonh.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/linux.jpg" width="640" /></a></div>
<br />
<br />
<br />
<div class="p1">
to estimate file space usage—space used under a particular directory or files on a file system.<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>du &lt;file or dir&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
<span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">PS: "./ means current directory"</span><br />
To run a file/program in current dir<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>./&lt;filename&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
To run a file/program in parent dir<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>../&lt;filename&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
To find a running process<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>ps aux | grep &lt;processName&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
To force kill process<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>kill -9 &lt;pid&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
To hangup a process<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>kill -HUP &lt;pid&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
To suspend a process<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>Ctrl+Z&nbsp; &nbsp; OR&nbsp; &nbsp;kill -STOP &lt;pid&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
To resume a process<br />
<br />
<ul>
<li><b>kill -CONT &lt;pid&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<br />
To give output of 1 program as an input to another do example give output of program1 as an input to program or pipe output of program1 to program<br />
<div>
To run a process/program in background:</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>program1 arg2program1 | program2</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To run a process/program in background:</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>processName</b></li>
<li><b>[Ctrl+Z]</b></li>
<li><b>bg&nbsp;</b><span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">//resumes suspended jobs while keeping them running in the background</span></li>
</ul>
<div>
To switch a process back to foreground</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>fg</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To become root do</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>sudo su</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To rename a file in linux</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>mv (option) &lt;filename1.ext&gt; &lt;filename2.ext&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To move 1 file to another location do:</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>mv &lt;file&gt; &lt;destination&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To move multiple files or dirs to another location do:</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>mv -t &lt;destination&gt; &lt;file1&gt; &lt;file2&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To delete multiple files inside a folder recursively, with same prefix or name or something similar do:</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>find . -name “*.&lt;ext&gt;” -type f -delete</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To copy all files and folder from 1 location to another</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>cp -a &lt;source&gt;. &lt;destination&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To look for a file with some extension</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>find . -name *.&lt;ext&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To look for a folder with some extension</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>find / -name &lt;folder name&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
find out what filesystems are mounted by running the command:</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>mount</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To view all devices on computer</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>lsblk</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To remove or add new partition to disk</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>fdisk /dev/sd&lt;a/b/whatever&gt;&nbsp; OR parted /dev/sd&lt;a/b/whatever&gt;</b></li>
<li><b>vi /etc/fstab </b><span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">and add or remove the partition from there</span></li>
</ul>
<div>
To create a new filesystem for a disk</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>mkfs.ext4 /dev/&lt;partition name like sdb1&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To mount a storage device or filesystem to existing directory</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>mount&nbsp; /dev/&lt;partition name like sdb1&gt;&nbsp; </b><span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">&lt;folder where to mount&gt;(to mount)</span></li>
<li><b>umount&nbsp; /&lt;dir name&gt; </b><span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">(to unmount)</span></li>
</ul>
<div>
To make a swap&nbsp;</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>swapoff -a&nbsp;</b><span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">&nbsp;(turn off swap space for all)</span></li>
<li><b>mkswap /dev/sda2&nbsp;</b><span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">(sets up a Linux swap area on a device or in a file.)&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><b>swapon /dev/&lt;partition name like sdb1&gt;&nbsp;</b><span style="color: #666666; font-size: x-small;">(turn swap swap space on again)</span></li>
</ul>
<h2>
CHANGING FILE PERMISSIONS</h2>
</div>
<div>
To give user access to read and write only for specific dir or file</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>chmod u+rw &lt;locationalbob&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To remove permission to execute all files and subfolders inside a dir and including the dir</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>chmod -R u-x &lt;location&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
To check file permissions of dir</div>
</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>ls -ld &lt;dir&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<div>
<div>
To check file permissions of dir and all sub-dirs and files inside it</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><b>ls -al &lt;dir&gt;</b></li>
</ul>
<h3>
<b>Identities</b></h3>
<div>
<style type="text/css">
p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #454545}
</style>


<br />
<div class="p1">
<b>u —&gt; the user who owns the file (that is, the owner)</b></div>
<div class="p1">
<b>g —&gt; the group to which the user belongs</b></div>
<div class="p1">
<b>o —&gt; others (not the owner or the owner's group)</b></div>
<div class="p1">
<b>a —&gt; everyone or all (u, g, and o)</b></div>
<h3>
<b>Permissions</b></h3>
<div class="p1">
<b>r —&gt; read access</b></div>
<div class="p1">
<b>w —&gt; write accessls<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></b></div>
<div class="p1">
<b>x —&gt; execute access</b></div>
<h3>
<b>Actions</b></h3>
<div class="p1">
<b>+ —&gt; adds the permission</b></div>
<div class="p1">
<b>- —&gt; removes the permission</b></div>
<div class="p1">
<b>= —&gt; makes it the only permission</b><br />
<b><br /></b>
